x4freetext: Isochronous cyclotron U-240
The self-supporting targets made of Ni-58(5.4 mg/cm**2)
or Ni-64 (4.5 mg/cm**2)were used.
The charged particles were recorded by six
semiconductor telescopes connected in coincidence.
Two telescopes consisted each of a silicon surface-
barrier deltaE detector 1 mm thick and Si(Li) E
detector 3 mm thick, which were set at 22.5 degree on
opposite sides of the beam axis, solid angles 1.3*10-3
and 2.4*10-3 sr. There were four telescopes on mobile
platforms, each consisting of a silicon surface-
barrier deltaE detector 50 micro-m thick, a 200 micro-m
and 1000 deltaE detector, and a 1 and 3 mm E-detector.
